<h1>Marc Jenkins</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="https://marcjenkins.co.uk/now">marcjenkins.co.uk/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Redditch
England
United Kingdom
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Freelance web developer at 16by9.
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I build websites.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I build websites because I love working on the web. I like that the web is open. I like that it’s always changing, always improving. That suits my iterative nature. I like to tinker, to deconstruct things to see how they’re built, and I like to learn new things. The web is a great place to do just that.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
You get more out of a relationship if you expect nothing in return. Give freely and the world has a way of paying you back.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
The Brain Audit by Sean D'Souza.
</p>

